What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Vacuum Insulation Market?

Market Analysis and Size

The vacuum insulated panels have largely witnessed popularity across the globe owing to its ability to conserve energy but also help to reduce carbon dioxide emissions. For instance, the international organizations, such as the International Energy Agency, have promoted and advised the use of vacuum insulated panels to reduce carbon emissions. As a result of these factors, the vacuum insulated panels market is expected to grow at a rapid pace over the forecast period as well.

Global vacuum insulation market was valued at USD 7.80 billion in 2021 and is expected to reach USD 11.84 billion by 2029, registering a CAGR of 5.36% during the forecast period of 2022-2029. In addition to the market insights such as market value, growth rate, market segments, geographical coverage, market players, and market scenario, the market report curated by the Data Bridge Market Research team also includes in-depth expert analysis, import/export analysis, pricing analysis, production consumption analysis, and climate chain scenario.

